ibrary at Nanterre</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_44563b58ed65ce215ae215d3865c4554" level="file"><did><unittitle>PRO - PREM 314 + FO</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1945/1945">1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_c627cbfb44fbed713e3d32090940f7d0" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c10af9c902dbaeb45f329ecd1b676efc" parent="aspace_c627cbfb44fbed713e3d32090940f7d0" type="folder">5-6</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_669fb89da0b2e7f65b08d266a15294ea"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Classified documents on French Indo-China from Public Records Office (Foreign Office documents)</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_40e26f05a69d014871b2b4106e486296" level="file"><did><unittitle>Mary Speers' Notes</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1942/1943" type="inclusive">1942-1943</unitdate><container id="aspace_5e6162887476fee3a76a3ae33dcf17ff" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_eb9896b513023fa8044eecc1ab94f6ea" parent="aspace_5e6162887476fee3a76a3ae33dcf17ff" type="folder">7</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_2fb37c646720f4ad11ac37885ab965b4"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Foreign Office series 371/35921, ff. Mostly on wartime relations with France.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_66374441566d62f006507bd57881470f" level="file"><did><unittitle>My Notes 1980 - PRO &amp; Rhodes House</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1980/1980">1980</unitdate><container id="aspace_fd15bed73ff07ed1bbf2ae4e2dff2043" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_e5b47ac0ec48e1feda4b1168248df55c" parent="aspace_fd15bed73ff07ed1bbf2ae4e2dff2043" type="folder">8</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_15da68ac1d332fa320352b6d9de99815"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>CAB 121/741 - Notes taken on memos on Indochina for PM from Foreign Section. File: "M